1- startsWith() --> takes one parameter and if the string is starting with given value return true 
2- endsWith()  --> return type of this method is boolean 
3- equals() --> returns boolean result

String name="computer"; 

name.equals("computer"); --> True
name.equals("Computer"); --> false

4- equalsIgnoreCase() --> takes one parameter as string value and returns boolean result

name.equalsIgnoreCase("COMPUTER"); --> true

6- substring() --> there are two implementation of substring method in java. Return type of substring method is String

sout(name.substring(3)); --> puter

name.toUpperCase(); 

sout(name); --> computer

sout(name.substring(2, 6)); 2,3,4,5
sout(name.substring(4,10)); 4,5,...8,9 --> stringindexoutofboundexception
name.substring(4,2); --> stringindexoutofboundexception
name.substring(4,4); --> empty string str=""

