int num=10; 

num=num+10; 20 

num+=10; --> compound assignment

num++; 

sout(num); 

boolean isLightOn=false;

!islightOn --> reverse the boolean value 


==========================================

7- replace(String oldChar, String newChar) --> replace method change oldChar with newChar and returns the String value. 

There are two implementation of replace method  


replace(String oldChar, String newChar); ""

replace(char oldChar, char newChar); ''

String str="Replace Method"; 

sout(str.replace("ace", "aced"));-->  Replaced Method

sout(str); --> Replace Method(String is immutable)

str=str.replace("e","k"); --> replace method will change all matching "e" with "k"; 

--> Rkplack Mkthod

str.replace("z", "r"); --> since we don't have "z" inside our string, it will not replace anything. 

8 trim() --> trim method trim the spaces in the beginning and at the end of our String. Trim method returns string value. Trim method will not delete the space between the words

String str="     Success is the target      "; 

sout(str.trim()); 


METHOD CHAINING

String fullName="  MuammeR TuraN - Instructor  "; 

fullName=fullName.toUpperCase(); --> will change the String with Upper Case 

"  MUAMMER TURAN - INSTRUCTOR  "

fullName=fullName.replace("-","/")

"  MUAMMER TURAN / INSTRUCTOR  "

fullName=fullName.trim(); 

"MUAMMER TURAN / INSTRUCTOR"


fullName=fullName.toUpperCase().replace("-","/").trim();

