IF STATEMENT(Conditional Statement)

if(booleanCondition){
	
	// write the code to execute
}

---> We use curly braces to execute block of code in java. Between curly braces is also called scope in java. 


int x=10; 
int y=5; 

if(x>y){
	
	sout(x is bigger than y); // it will be executed if my condition is true. 
}

